Add local Streamlit UI for the A->F flow

Add a thin local single-user UI under src/shorts_pipeline/ui/. The Streamlit
entry point (app.py) only renders; all orchestration lives in a Streamlit-free
controller (controller.py) that composes the existing phase services, selects
providers (default deterministic fake, opt-in real), and exposes read helpers.

The controller is fully unit tested (full A->F path, stage-by-stage status
progression, provider selection, status events, D payload construction). The
Streamlit layer is verified by a manual checklist in docs/06 and is not imported
by the test suite, since the optional ui extra is not installed in CI.

No network egress: B and E use fake providers unless the explicit real-LLM
opt-in is configured. No rendering, TTS, upload, or external .kdenlive trust.

Update docs/06 (UI controller tests and a Streamlit manual checklist), docs/07
(inventory, coverage, and the now-accurate UI architecture note), and README
with local UI usage.

